        Official Singles Chart on 20/1/2017

        20 January 2017 - 26 January 2017

        The Official UK Singles Chart reflects the UKs biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1 and MTV, the Top 100 is published exclusively on OfficialCharts.com. View the biggest songs of 2024 so far.

        another good week for the charts today ;)
        nice to see Ed Sheeran hold #1 and #2 again, hopefully Shape Of You can at least near Rockabye's number of weeks at no1.
        Great to see You Don't Know Me continuing to rise up the charts. It's a great song and I'm sure it'll overtake Rag 'N' Bone man into no3 next week as that's where it is in both Spotify and iTunes right now. I can see it eventually overtaking Castle on the hill in to no2 in the coming weeks too!
        Call On Me continuing to rise is great as is JP Cooper holding onto a top 10 spot. I discovered September Song in October and always liked it, so I'm really glad it finally became a hit!
        I like Paris and am glad it has become The Chainsmokers' 3rd Top 10 hit, and first top 10 debut
        I love the fact that Bad Things continues to climb rapidly, at this rate it could be no12 or 11 next week or maybe reach top 10! its currently just outside top 10 on iTunes and is still climbing on Spotify, yet to reach top 20. I knew it from its first week released in October and am extremely happy it finally became a big hit over here!
        No Lie and Shed A light are both great songs, especially the latter, which I've known since both their releases in November, and like September Song, Call on me and Bad Things, am happy they're getting big hits!
        As you can probably tell I'm really excited with the charts right now, as lots of big songs are climbing and Ed Sheeran's releases too. I literally think these past 2 weeks have been more exciting than any 2 in 2016! hopefully the new rule can help the charts stay this exciting all year round!
        I like Now And later, and am happy it reached top 40. Bad and Boujee is ok nut it might grow on me. it reminds me of Black Beatles just with less talented rappers, but I really liked Black Beatles so that can only be a good thing!
        Another thing I'm really excited about is the fact that Not In Love by M.O entered as high as 61. I love the song- its another one i've known from its release in early December and always loved. its one of my favourite songs right now and I really hope it reaches top 40!
        I'm not too sure on Be The One right now, especially as it was initially released as Dua Lipa's second single in 2015, but I'm sure it'll grow on me as I liked her other two chart hits.
        Nathan Sykes gets his fifth top 70 hit with There's Only One Of You, which is another good release following Kiss Me Quick, Over And Over Again, Give It Up and Famous. that's likely to climb especially as it has literally no streaming right now.
        I don't really care too much about the 's new album, especially as I don't like On Hold, but I might check out Say Something loving as that's been fluttering around the Spotify top 50 all this week. I probably won't like it too much though. Congratulations to them for reaching no1 though!
        on the whole, another fantastic week for the charts this week! 2017 has been amazing, with climbers, new entries galore and Ed Sheeran! I think 2017 will be fantastic if it remains like this all year round.
        One of the things which makes me love the climbers so much Is that ive known all of them since they were released in October, November etc so have watched them rise!
        Thank you for reading! ;)

        My thoughts & observations on the UK charts as always
        - As expected, Ed Sheeran takes the Top 2 spots on the singles chart once again; Shape Of You at #1 (66k sales & 11M streams) & Castle On The Hill at #2 (49k sales & 7.8M streams). Unless there is another big artist returning soon, then I dont see this changing for a few weeks yet. My current prediction is 6+ weeks at #1 for the former of these songs.
        - While the former has much higher sales & streaming figures, the latter actually had greater airplay this week & was trending more on YouTube. To update my ratings of both songs from last week, Shape Of You rises to a 7/10 & Castle On The Hill remains at a 9/10.
        - You Dont Know Me by Jax Jones ft RAYE has already become of the biggest party & club anthems to start 2017, as it continues to ascend in the Top 10 (9-4). Its going to take a lot to challenge Ed Sheeran, but if any song can do it thats in the charts right now, this is it!
        - The Chainsmokers earn their sixth UK Top 40 single with the debut of Paris at #10. Interestingly, this becomes the EDM duos highest debuting song on the UK charts. If you liked Closer (which spent four weeks at #1 in September), then youll probably enjoy this too. While there is no big drop to this unlike The Chainsmokers previous dance hits, I really like the vocalist (Emily Warren) here.
        - No Lie by Sean Paul ft Dua Lipa (28-21) & Bad Things by Machine Gun Kelly & Camila Cabello (23-16) tie for the biggest climbers in the Top 40 this week. I think Bad Things may have a chance at entering the Top 10 within the coming weeks. :)
        - There were two more new arrivals & one returning song in the Top 40 this week. The first of them being Bad & Boujee by Migos ft Lil Uzi Vert (50-37). This has already been #1 in the US & there are a couple of reasons for its success; 1) Donald Glover gave it a mention at the Globen Globes & 2) the meme involving the rain drop, drop top lyrics in the song. Other than the decent production by Metro Boomin, theres really not a lot of positives I can say about this; Migos rapping parts are so boring & Lil Uzi Vert's verse is just completely awful; the first part of it is incomprehensible & the second half of it is so dull. Thats why I really hope this doesnt become a hit here.
        - Meanwhile, The re-enter the Top 40 with On Hold (74-34). This is thanks to the bands third album, I See You, being released. I See You also just became the groups second #1 over on the albums chart, accumulating 26,500 total units in the first week of its release.
        - The rest of the Top 5 on the albums chart is; Glory Days by Little Mix (1-2), La La Lands Motion Picture Cast Recording (99-3!), Ladies & Gentlemen The Best Of by George Michael (stationary at #4) & Migration by Bonobo (debuts at #5).
        - Now & Later by Sage The Gemini is also new to the Top 40 today (43-32), which I certainly dont mind after first listen & may grow on me even further. You may remember him from his feature on Flo Ridas GDFR, which peaked at #3 in March 2015.
        - Finally, Mr Brightside by The Killers is now spending its 156th week inside the Top 100. If it can remain in the chart for 10 more weeks, then It will tie the record for the longest a song has spent in the singles chart. The current record holders are Snow Patrol with Chasing Cars (166 weeks).
        - Thanks for reading my review everyone. Have a great weekend!
